LABEL: NONMEM Comment Flag
NOTE: Derived. C="C" when meet below conditions: CNINCFL=N; No post dose above LLOQ concentration; missing elapsed time; Pre first dose concentration > LLOQ.

LABEL: Reason for exclusion
NOTE: CFLAG=CNEXCRSN if CNINCFL="N", reason for other exclusion otherwise.

LABEL: Actual Elapsed Time from 1st Dose (day)
NOTE: Derived.  Time of sample collection date/time (APCDTM)  to first dose date/time (RFSTDTM) if both not missing; if RFSTDTM=. Then use the first infusion end time-1800 for TIME calculation;  TIME=(APCDT-RFSTDT )+pctptnum/24; otherwise =APCDT-RFSTDT;

LABEL: Nominal Elapsed Time from 1st Dose (day)
NOTE: Derived, Difference from planned visit, time point to the first dose visit.

LABEL: Time Since Last Dose (day)
NOTE: Derived. Time of sample collection date/time (APCDTM) to previous infusion start date and time if both available, Use APCDT and last infusiondate otherwise.

LABEL: Nominal Time Since Last Dose (day)
NOTE: Derived, Difference from planned visit, time point to the previous dose visit.

LABEL: Drug  Concentration (mg/L)
NOTE: DVOR=1/2*PCLLOQ if AVAL=0 and TIME <=0; DVOR=AVAL otherwise

LABEL: PK Concentration <LLOQ
NOTE: FBLQ=1 if DVOR=0.039, FBLQ=0 if DVOR> 0.039

LABEL: Cumulated Dose Amount (mg)
NOTE: Cumulated the dose administrated at each infusion visit (ADEX.EXDOSMG)

LABEL: Referece Dose Number
NOTE: Derived. Dose number associated to the previous infusion according to the elapsed time

LABEL: Body Weight (kg)
NOTE: ISS.ADVS .Select paramcd="WEIGHT"  and anl01fl="Y",  use the last non missing WGT if WGT missing at current visit ; use baseline weight if cycle 1 day 1  WGT is missing.

LABEL: Tumor Type ((coded)
NOTE:
Derived. For study 1423,TUMTYPE2=scan (arm, 2, '-'); Further mapping  if index(tumtype2, 'CSCC') then tumtype2=tr01pg3;
  if cohort="DE" then tumtype2=tumtype; For 1540: coded as laCSCC if group=2; as mCSCC otherwise.

LABEL: CSCC Population (1540)
NOTE: Numeric value of ISS.ADSL.CSCCP2FL for study 1423; set=1 for study 1540

LABEL: PK Efficacy CSCC Analysis Set
NOTE: Derived.  PKEFCSCC="Y" if ADSL.FASCSFL="Y" and PKFL="Y"; "N" otherwise

LABEL: PK Safety CSCC Analysis Set
NOTE: Derived.  PKSFCSCC="Y" if ADSL.SAFFL="Y" and PKFL="Y" and TR01PK3="CSCC Patients"; "N" otherwise

LABEL: Concomitant Systemic Cortisteroids
NOTE:
Derived according to the systemic corticorsteroids list. CORTFLN=1 if cmdecod in ( 'CORTICOSTEROID NOS', 'CORTICOSTEROIDS', 'CORTISONE','DEXAMETHASONE', 'DEXAMETHASONE SODIUM PHOSPHATE','HYDROCORTISONE',
'METHYLPREDNISOLONE','METHYLPREDNISOLONE SODIUM SUCCINATE','PREDNISOLONE','PREDNISONE'); 0 otherwise.

LABEL: Duration of Infusion (day)
NOTE: Cumulated duration of infusion at each infusion visit

LABEL: Missed Dose
NOTE: Derived. MISSDFL="Dose not given" if at planned infusion visit the AMT<=0.

LABEL: Dose after last available conc.
NOTE: Derived. Dose record is after the last available concentration record.

LABEL: ADA status
NOTE: Derived from pooled ADISADA dataset from study 1423 and 1540. ADASTA=ADISADA.AVAL select ADISADA.PARAM = 'ADA Status'

LABEL: Maximum Titer
NOTE: Derived from pooled ADISADA dataset from study 1423 and 1540. TITER=ADISADA.AVAL select ADISADA.paramcd =" Treatment-emergent/boosted Max. Titer"

LABEL: Maximum Titer Category
NOTE: Derived from pooled ADISADA dataset from study 1423 and 1540. MAXTCAT=ADISADA.AVALC select ADISADA.paramcd =" Treatment-emergent/boosted Max. Titer CAT"

LABEL: Neutralized AB status
NOTE: Derived from pooled ADISADA dataset from study 1423 and 1540. NABSTA=ADISADA.AVAL select ADISADA.PARAM = 'Neutralizing Status'

LABEL: Imputed Baseline ALB (g/L)
NOTE: If ALBBL is missing, IALBBL= Median of ALBBL within study

LABEL: Albumin (g/L)
NOTE: ISS.ADLB.AVAL select PARAMCD="ALB" and ADY >=1 and ANL01FL="Y";  take the last non missing value If ALB missing at current visit; use baseline ALB if cycle 1 day 1 ALB is missing.

LABEL: Imputed Baseline LDH (IU/L)
NOTE: If LDHBL is missing, ILDHBL= Median of LDHBL within study

LABEL: LDH (IU/L)
NOTE: ISS.ADLB.AVAL select PARAMCD="LDH" and ADY >=1 and ANL01FL="Y"; take the last non missing value If LDH missing at current visit;  use baseline LDH  if cycle 1 day 1 LDH is missing.

LABEL: Imputed Baseline ALT (IU/L)
NOTE: If ALTBL is missing, IALTBL= Median of ALTBL within study

LABEL: Imputed Baseline IGG (g/L)
NOTE: If IGGBL is missing, IIGGBL= Median of IGGBL within study

LABEL: Imputed Baseline BILI (umol/L)
NOTE: If BILIBL is missing, IBILIBL =Median of BILIBL within study
